The death of veteran struggle lawyer George Bizos has left many heartbroken. Courtesy #DStv403. JOHANNESBURG - Flags will fly at half-mast from Saturday to honour human rights lawyer George Bizos. President Cyril Ramaphosa declared that Bizos is to receive a Special Official Funeral. READ: George Bizos talks on Madiba and their friendship He described him as one of the best legal minds in the country who contributed to the fight for democracy. Bizos died on Wednesday at the age 92. IN PICTURES: Remembering George Bizos Flags will fly at half-mast until his funeral on Thursday. Bizos was famously part of the legal team that defended Nelson Mandela, Govan Mbeki and Walter Sisulu at the Rivonia Treason Trial from 1963-64.